          <Base:Description type="brief">
             stacked stone fireplace
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="examine">
             A large stacked stone fireplace with a slate mantel.  It has a wide mouth with an arched top and is flanked on either side by stacked stones.  The slate mantel above is a foot deep and ends above the stones on either side of the hearth.  Inside the fireplace is an iron rack holding a small pile of logs above a grating on the floor of the fireplace.  The chimney continues above the fireplace to the floors above. {? | $(this.trait:lit) |The fireplace is currently lit.}
          </Base:Description>
          <Base:Description type="look">
             A large stacked stone fireplace with a slate mantel.{? | $(this.trait:lit) |The fireplace is currently lit.}
          </Base:Description>
